slumber, and we now know

17
00:01:53,195 --> 00:01:55,195
that they intend to do
something horrible to Japan.

18
00:01:56,783 --> 00:01:57,242
But what?

19
00:01:57,784 --> 00:01:58,784
Nobody knows.

20
00:01:58,868 --> 00:01:59,930
And the danger continues to grow

21
00:01:59,954 --> 00:02:01,514
as more and more of
the root like plants

22
00:02:02,164 --> 00:02:03,365
keep emerging from the ground.

23
00:02:03,832 --> 00:02:05,473
The key to solving the
mystery seems to be

24
00:02:05,750 --> 00:02:07,351
the Amano Iwato, the
cave of the Sun God,

25
00:02:08,712 --> 00:02:10,873
which we think is located in
my old home town of Izumo.

26
00:02:12,507 --> 00:02:13,708
But we can't find it anywhere.

27
00:02:14,259 --> 00:02:15,979
Together with Mr.
Kunikida and Ms. Takeuchi,

28
00:02:17,096 --> 00:02:18,936
I've returned to Izumo
to search for the Iwato.

29
00:02:20,515 --> 00:02:22,035
And there's someone
else here, as well.

30
00:02:22,350 --> 00:02:24,270
For some time now, I've
been sensing the presence

31
00:02:25,938 --> 00:02:27,298
of Kusanagi in the
back of my mind.

32
00:02:28,648 --> 00:02:29,231
It's so strange.

33
00:02:29,232 --> 00:02:30,672
Even though we're
really miles apart,

34
00:02:30,900 --> 00:02:33,021
sometimes it's as if he was
standing right next to me.

35
00:02:34,237 --> 00:02:35,757
Kusanagi thinks that
we share this link

36
00:02:35,864 --> 00:02:38,105
because of our mitamas, which
came from the same Aragami.

37
00:02:39,241 --> 00:02:40,442
But maybe it's something more.

38
00:02:41,703 --> 00:02:42,454
If we get through this alive,

39
00:02:42,620 --> 00:02:44,661
once we've finally beaten
Susana-Oh and the Aragami,

40
00:02:45,247 --> 00:02:47,407
maybe we'll have time to get
to know each other better.

41
00:02:47,917 --> 00:02:49,918
To do the sort of things
normal people do together.

42
00:02:51,337 --> 00:02:52,498
I think I'd really like that.

43
00:02:55,925 --> 00:02:56,925
Goodbye?

44
00:02:57,178 --> 00:02:57,469
No way!

45
00:02:57,635 --> 00:02:58,635
A Tearful farewell?

46
00:03:01,263 --> 00:03:02,263
(wind howling)

47
00:03:08,063 --> 00:03:09,063
My diary.

48
00:03:10,272 --> 00:03:11,513
I haven't written in it at all.

49
00:03:12,193 --> 00:03:13,193
Not since I met...

50
00:03:14,276 --> 00:03:14,527
(gasp)

51
00:03:15,029 --> 00:03:16,029
Kasanagi.

52
00:03:17,906 --> 00:03:19,147
Lord Susana-Oh and I must leave

53
00:03:21,076 --> 00:03:22,076
for the last Iwato.

54
00:03:22,952 --> 00:03:23,952
(gasp) The Iwato!

55
00:03:24,496 --> 00:03:25,164
But where?

56
00:03:25,287 --> 00:03:26,724
Marakumo, I'll trust
you to make sure

57
00:03:26,748 --> 00:03:28,028
