98
00:04:57,379 --> 00:04:57,839
But, why?

99
00:04:58,380 --> 00:04:58,965
(sobbing)

100
00:04:59,133 --> 00:05:00,613
Why is Katy doing
something like this?

101
00:05:01,009 --> 00:05:02,130
Why did she go to Susano-Oh?

102
00:05:03,011 --> 00:05:04,651
The Kusanada is supposed
to protect Japan.

103
00:05:06,388 --> 00:05:06,723
(crying)

104
00:05:07,224 --> 00:05:08,224
I don't understand.

105
00:05:08,892 --> 00:05:09,892
Why Katy?

106
00:05:10,435 --> 00:05:11,435
Why?

107
00:05:11,936 --> 00:05:12,936
(continues sobbing)

108
00:05:16,733 --> 00:05:18,534
If we follow the reactions
of Momiji's Matama,

109
00:05:20,402 --> 00:05:21,962
I'm sure that we can
find the Iwato that

110
00:05:22,697 --> 00:05:23,858
Susano-Oh is heading towards.

111
00:05:24,490 --> 00:05:25,490
I suppose it might work.

112
00:05:29,121 --> 00:05:30,121
Huh?

113
00:05:33,167 --> 00:05:34,167
Oh, thanks.

114
00:05:35,668 --> 00:05:36,170
Roar!

115
00:05:36,337 --> 00:05:37,605
Just making sure
that you're alert.

116
00:05:37,629 --> 00:05:39,870
I'm just trying to take your
mind off your problems, sir.

117
00:05:40,590 --> 00:05:42,070
Yesterday may have
been long and hard,

118
00:05:42,425 --> 00:05:44,025
but I'm sure something
will come up today

119
00:05:45,262 --> 00:05:46,302
if we put our minds to it.

120
00:05:47,889 --> 00:05:48,473
That's a good point,

121
00:05:48,640 --> 00:05:49,960
we can't let the
stress get to us.

122
00:05:50,432 --> 00:05:51,673
We ought to relieve it somehow.

123
00:05:53,187 --> 00:05:53,436
You bet!

124
00:05:53,978 --> 00:05:54,978
