131
00:06:13,665 --> 00:06:14,665
Um, we're still looking.

132
00:06:15,083 --> 00:06:16,683
Would you mind hurrying
this up a little?

133
00:06:18,086 --> 00:06:19,207
Just be quiet and follow me.

134
00:06:20,422 --> 00:06:21,422
Yes, Grandma.

135
00:06:24,008 --> 00:06:24,466
Huh?

136
00:06:24,759 --> 00:06:25,759
What is that?

137
00:06:26,678 --> 00:06:27,678
(dramatic music plays)

138
00:06:34,269 --> 00:06:35,429
This is the Aiashi No Hokora,

139
00:06:36,271 --> 00:06:37,271
the cave of restoration.

140
00:06:37,479 --> 00:06:39,159
It's the birth right
of the Fujumia family,

141
00:06:40,192 --> 00:06:41,352
the family of the Gushinadas.

142
00:06:41,483 --> 00:06:42,763
Nobody knows much
more than that.

143
00:06:44,196 --> 00:06:45,196
Not even me.

144
00:06:45,487 --> 00:06:45,947
Oh.

145
00:06:46,488 --> 00:06:47,729
This is what we're looking for.

146
00:06:48,825 --> 00:06:49,825
Why didn't you tell us?

147
00:06:50,827 --> 00:06:52,708
Sorry, this place has
been in the family so long

148
00:06:52,996 --> 00:06:54,997
we don't even think of it
as being unusual anymore.

149
00:06:56,498 --> 00:06:57,619
This must be the last Iwato.

150
00:06:58,751 --> 00:06:59,420
It's possible.

151
00:06:59,669 --> 00:07:00,750
Well, I've shown it to you.

152
00:07:01,629 --> 00:07:02,629
The rest is up to you.

153
00:07:03,089 --> 00:07:03,506
Mrs. Fujimia?

154
00:07:03,673 --> 00:07:05,713
You must do whatever you
think is best, Mr. Unakita.

155
00:07:08,970 --> 00:07:09,970
(groans)

156
00:07:12,932 --> 00:07:13,516
I understand, sir.

157
00:07:13,850 --> 00:07:15,650
I'll keep searching for
Susano-Oh with Momiji.

158
00:07:16,311 --> 00:07:18,351
Her Matama should let us
know when he's in the area.

159
00:07:18,520 --> 00:07:20,080
I'm sorry about the
change in our plans.

160
00:07:21,107 --> 00:07:22,707
I've just got a feeling
about this place.

161
00:07:24,319 --> 00:07:24,569
Sir?

162
00:07:25,069 --> 00:07:25,527
Huh?

163
00:07:25,778 --> 00:07:26,778
Oh, thanks.

164
00:07:28,865 --> 00:07:30,465
I'm just glad you're
feeling better, sir.

165
00:07:31,533 --> 00:07:32,533
You look better, too.

166
00:07:32,994 --> 00:07:33,994
Full of hope.

167
00:07:35,537 --> 00:07:36,122
I am, huh?

168
00:07:36,539 --> 00:07:37,206
(giggles)

169
00:07:37,374 --> 00:07:39,294
I've got to contact the
Izumo Self-Defense Force,

170
00:07:39,460 --> 00:07:40,043
but, I'll see you later.

171
00:07:40,209 --> 00:07:42,170
Well, I think that we can
keep ourselves occupied.

172
00:07:42,544 --> 00:07:43,825
But in case your hunch is wrong,

173
00:07:44,256 --> 00:07:45,816
we'll keep an eye out
for strange caves.

174
00:07:46,883 --> 00:07:47,384
Yeah!

175
00:07:47,549 --> 00:07:49,404
This Eragami detector
will find Susano-Oh first!

176
00:07:49,428 --> 00:07:51,508
Mrs. Takiuchi, you're not
gonna let him score on you,

177
00:07:52,554 --> 00:07:52,889
are you?

178
00:07:53,432 --> 00:07:53,681
Uh...

179
00:07:53,890 --> 00:07:54,556
You're in charge.

180
00:07:54,766 --> 00:07:55,766
- [Momiji] Roger!

181
00:07:55,892 --> 00:07:56,892
(tires squealing)

182
00:08:03,983 --> 00:08:04,983
Hmmm.

183
00:08:06,152 --> 00:08:07,152
(dramatic music)

184
00:08:14,952 --> 00:08:15,952
(grunting)

185
00:08:20,582 --> 00:08:20,917
Damn!

186
00:08:21,084 --> 00:08:22,444
Why must you float
around so much?!

187
00:08:22,710 --> 00:08:23,710
(laughs menacingly)

188
00:08:24,712 --> 00:08:25,712
Come on!

189
00:08:26,047 --> 00:08:27,047
(dramatic music)

190
00:08:27,799 --> 00:08:28,799
(explosions)

191
00:08:54,075 --> 00:08:54,616
Look at this.

192
00:08:54,659 --> 00:08:56,019
This city was such
a peaceful place

193
00:08:56,744 --> 00:08:57,785
until just a few days ago.

194
00:08:58,580 --> 00:08:59,597
What's going to become of Japan?

195
00:08:59,621 --> 00:09:01,101
Why don't you ask
one of these things?

196
00:09:02,624 --> 00:09:03,624
(groans)

197
00:09:06,963 --> 00:09:07,963
Come on!

198
00:09:08,630 --> 00:09:09,048
Get a move on!

199
00:09:09,508 --> 00:09:10,508
Grab that ammo!

200
00:09:10,758 --> 00:09:11,593
Get your butts in...!

201
00:09:11,634 --> 00:09:13,634
[helicopter pilot] Offensive
engine is in position!

202
00:09:14,596 --> 00:09:15,596
Division in range!

203
00:09:15,637 --> 00:09:16,637
(whirring)

204
00:09:27,609 --> 00:09:28,609
Susano-Oh is coming.

205
00:09:32,447 --> 00:09:34,247
When that time comes,
can I really shoot Katy?

206
00:09:38,327 --> 00:09:38,911
(sad music plays)

207
00:09:39,120 --> 00:09:40,120
Hey, are you ready?

208
00:09:40,746 --> 00:09:41,415
Say "limburger!"

209
00:09:41,663 --> 00:09:43,343
- [Katy] Come on, Dad,
don't make me laugh.

210
00:09:45,168 --> 00:09:46,728
(laughs) But everyone
prefers the way you look

211
00:09:46,752 --> 00:09:48,672
when you smiling to that
pouty face you're making

212
00:09:50,632 --> 00:09:51,048
right now.

213
00:09:51,215 --> 00:09:51,966
I don't like it when I laugh.

214
00:09:52,133 --> 00:09:53,334
I always end up looking weird.

215
00:09:53,552 --> 00:09:54,552
Okay, cheese!

216
00:09:54,844 --> 00:09:55,344
Cheese.

217
00:09:55,677 --> 00:09:56,137
(gunshot)

218
00:09:56,678 --> 00:09:57,678
(gasps)

219
00:10:05,564 --> 00:10:05,813
Katy.

220
00:10:06,355 --> 00:10:07,556
It's a heavy burden, isn't it?

221
00:10:08,400 --> 00:10:09,400
Huh?

222
00:10:10,692 --> 00:10:11,692
Mrs. Fujimia.

223
00:10:11,777 --> 00:10:12,446
Hesitate,

224
00:10:12,613 --> 00:10:14,453
and you may cause the
end of all you hold dear.

225
00:10:16,575 --> 00:10:17,575
Huh?

226
00:10:18,452 --> 00:10:19,452
I understand.

227
00:10:22,955 --> 00:10:23,955
(sad music)

228
00:10:24,790 --> 00:10:26,230
Katy, I didn't want
to see you again.

229
00:10:27,586 --> 00:10:28,586
Not now, not like this.

230
00:10:29,588 --> 00:10:30,588
(sad music continues)

231
00:10:35,218 --> 00:10:36,218
It's hard.

232
00:10:36,428 --> 00:10:36,886
Mrs. Fujimia?

233
00:10:37,386 --> 00:10:39,027
Things are about to
happen all over Japan.

234
00:10:40,641 --> 00:10:42,121
But still, one mustn't
act too rashly.

235
00:10:43,725 --> 00:10:44,966
It's too easy to make mistakes.

236
00:10:46,728 --> 00:10:49,088
Ah, listen to me, talking to
myself, just like an old woman.

237
00:10:52,944 --> 00:10:53,944
(sighs)

238
00:10:55,154 --> 00:10:57,315
How were you able to survive
with such pathetic powers?

239
00:10:59,033 --> 00:11:00,033
(explosive music)

240
00:11:02,579 --> 00:11:04,899
(chuckles) How inconvenient it
must be to be unable to fly.

241
00:11:06,916 --> 00:11:08,396
An intelligent fighter
uses his brains

242
00:11:08,918 --> 00:11:10,358
to offset his physical
disadvantages.

243
00:11:13,256 --> 00:11:14,256
(dramatic music)

244
00:11:16,635 --> 00:11:17,995
I'm a lot better
than I used to be!

245
00:11:18,928 --> 00:11:19,928
Oh, sure!

246
00:11:20,762 --> 00:11:21,762
(upbeat music)

247
00:11:23,765 --> 00:11:25,285
Well, we've arrived
at our destination.

248
00:11:25,768 --> 00:11:27,408
So, I guess I ought
to start the ceremony.

249
00:11:28,354 --> 00:11:29,395
I hope you like surprises.

250
00:11:30,649 --> 00:11:30,898
What?

251
00:11:31,357 --> 00:11:32,357
(laughing)

252
00:11:33,985 --> 00:11:34,985
What the...?

253
00:11:37,196 --> 00:11:38,196
(ominous ringing)

254
00:11:39,198 --> 00:11:40,198
(whirring)

255
00:11:43,369 --> 00:11:44,369
Uh oh!

256
00:11:46,581 --> 00:11:48,541
Marakumo, what are you up
to now, you spiny freak?

257
00:11:51,877 --> 00:11:52,877
Moe, what are you doing?

258
00:11:53,755 --> 00:11:54,755
Forming a barrier.

259
00:11:54,964 --> 00:11:55,964
With her blood?

260
00:11:56,132 --> 00:11:56,675
Mmh.

261
00:11:56,798 --> 00:11:57,798
(high pitched ringing)

262
00:12:05,559 --> 00:12:06,559
(whirring)

263
00:12:06,934 --> 00:12:08,334
It's still coming
from way up ahead.

264
00:12:09,811 --> 00:12:10,396
What does the map say?

265
00:12:10,564 --> 00:12:12,644
Looks like we should take
Route 431 to Shinjiko Lake.

266
00:12:15,276 --> 00:12:15,777
Okay.

267
00:12:16,235 --> 00:12:17,436
Momiji, you look pretty eager.

268
00:12:18,739 --> 00:12:18,988
Mmm Hmm.

269
00:12:19,155 --> 00:12:21,076
I'm going to do my greatest
detective work today!

270
00:12:21,824 --> 00:12:22,491
You will, huh?

271
00:12:22,659 --> 00:12:24,579
Isn't it great when you
both share a common goal?

272
00:12:26,788 --> 00:12:27,788
Yeah!

273
00:12:29,791 --> 00:12:30,791
(water rushing)

274
00:12:37,298 --> 00:12:38,298
(screaming)

275
00:12:39,967 --> 00:12:40,468
What?

276
00:12:40,842 --> 00:12:41,842
What the hell was that?

277
00:12:44,930 --> 00:12:45,930
(ominous music)

278
00:12:51,853 --> 00:12:52,853
A mirror.

279
00:12:53,522 --> 00:12:55,323
(laughs menacingly) Our
great lord, Susano-Oh,

280
00:12:57,026 --> 00:12:58,706
will be arriving at
the Iwato any time now.

281
00:12:59,445 --> 00:13:01,446
And when the sun's rays
finally strike that mirror.

282
00:13:02,907 --> 00:13:04,587
The bells will announce
Susano-Oh's ritual.

283
00:13:05,867 --> 00:13:07,507
And toll a death knell
for the human race.

284
00:13:08,537 --> 00:13:10,298
And then the world of
the Aragami, our world,

285
00:13:12,416 --> 00:13:13,416
