286
00:13:13,875 --> 00:13:14,875
Not if I can help it!

287
00:13:19,507 --> 00:13:20,507
Aaaaaaargh!

288
00:13:23,595 --> 00:13:24,595
(dripping)

289
00:13:32,395 --> 00:13:33,395
Moe was once a Kushinada.

290
00:13:34,522 --> 00:13:34,896
Huh?

291
00:13:34,939 --> 00:13:36,579
The full power of her
line has been passed

292
00:13:36,858 --> 00:13:37,441
to Momiji's generation.

293
00:13:37,609 --> 00:13:39,529
But, there should be enough
left to make her seal

294
00:13:40,319 --> 00:13:41,319
worth that sacrifice.

295
00:13:41,696 --> 00:13:42,976
I know my blood can't stop them,

296
00:13:43,447 --> 00:13:44,447
but it might delay them.

297
00:13:47,159 --> 00:13:48,159
Hmmm.

298
00:13:48,910 --> 00:13:50,750
All the troops have taken
their positions, sir.

299
00:13:51,914 --> 00:13:52,581
Very good.

300
00:13:52,914 --> 00:13:53,914
Thank you, sir!

301
00:13:57,919 --> 00:13:58,919
(tapping)

302
00:14:00,757 --> 00:14:01,757
Susano-Oh is coming.

303
00:14:02,258 --> 00:14:03,538
I know he's coming
to this Iwato.

304
00:14:07,179 --> 00:14:08,420
The trees sense their presence.

305
00:14:11,434 --> 00:14:11,933
Yes.

306
00:14:12,059 --> 00:14:13,059
They're here!

307
00:14:19,941 --> 00:14:21,002
- [Soldier] There they are!

308
00:14:21,026 --> 00:14:21,695
Stop them!

309
00:14:21,862 --> 00:14:23,742
Don't move lady, or we'll
shoot you and the kid!

310
00:14:26,157 --> 00:14:27,157
(whirring)

311
00:14:27,949 --> 00:14:28,949
(crackling)

312
00:14:34,373 --> 00:14:35,373
Aah!

313
00:14:37,752 --> 00:14:38,752
(dramatic music)

314
00:14:39,961 --> 00:14:40,714
Momiji, what's wrong?

315
00:14:40,922 --> 00:14:41,922
Susano-Oh is over there!

316
00:14:42,924 --> 00:14:43,174
Huh?

317
00:14:43,340 --> 00:14:44,581
Then what have we been chasing?

318
00:14:44,966 --> 00:14:45,966
(whirring)

319
00:14:48,722 --> 00:14:50,842
What are you going to do
with this thing, you monster?

320
00:14:51,973 --> 00:14:53,253
I see no reason
to tell you that.

321
00:14:53,935 --> 00:14:55,735
I guess I'm going to
have to shatter it, then.

322
00:14:58,980 --> 00:14:59,273
Aaaaah!

323
00:14:59,981 --> 00:15:01,541
- [Marakumo] How dare
you interrupt me!

324
00:15:05,362 --> 00:15:06,362
(crashing)

325
00:15:13,995 --> 00:15:14,995
Kusanagi!

326
00:15:28,845 --> 00:15:29,261
I told you!

327
00:15:29,428 --> 00:15:31,349
I'm a little different
from the way I used to be.

328
00:15:32,013 --> 00:15:32,640
Quite impressive,

329
00:15:32,807 --> 00:15:34,087
you're not as weak
as I believed.

330
00:15:34,642 --> 00:15:35,803
And in appreciation for this,

331
00:15:37,102 --> 00:15:38,462
I'm going to stop
playing with you.

332
00:15:40,523 --> 00:15:41,523
Goodbye Kusanagi.

333
00:15:42,274 --> 00:15:42,943
Kusanagi!

334
00:15:43,024 --> 00:15:44,824
Momaiji, you've got to
get back to Izumo, now!

335
00:15:45,026 --> 00:15:46,626
If Katy and Susano-Oh
seal off the Iwato,

336
00:15:48,029 --> 00:15:49,029
it'll be all over!

337
00:15:49,866 --> 00:15:50,115
But you!

338
00:15:50,366 --> 00:15:52,006
Stop arguing with me
just get out of here!

339
00:15:53,327 --> 00:15:54,327
But, Kasanagi!

340
00:15:54,411 --> 00:15:55,411
Kasanagi!

341
00:15:56,664 --> 00:15:57,038
Momiji.

342
00:15:57,081 --> 00:15:58,641
Mrs Takeichi, we've
got to get back now!

343
00:16:04,547 --> 00:16:05,547
(gunfire)

344
00:16:09,050 --> 00:16:10,050
(screaming)

345
00:16:16,057 --> 00:16:17,057
(crackling)

346
00:16:21,564 --> 00:16:22,564
(sad music)

347
00:16:29,738 --> 00:16:30,859
Why must I see you this way?

348
00:16:32,073 --> 00:16:32,491
Perhaps the time

349
00:16:32,658 --> 00:16:34,338
and nature of this
meeting were inevitable.

350
00:16:35,619 --> 00:16:36,619
I had no choice.

351
00:16:37,663 --> 00:16:38,663
This is my destiny.

352
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:41,000
For I am the Kushinada.

353
00:16:42,501 --> 00:16:43,003
Huh.

354
00:16:43,127 --> 00:16:43,795
But, Katy,

355
00:16:44,004 --> 00:16:45,724
this technological
travesty that we live in,

356
00:16:46,798 --> 00:16:48,478
modern Japan, is an
assault upon my senses,

357
00:16:51,092 --> 00:16:52,812
an assault upon the
sanity of the Kushinada.

358
00:16:54,095 --> 00:16:55,455
The Kushinada is
Japan's protector.

359
00:16:59,100 --> 00:17:00,100
(explosion)

360
00:17:02,771 --> 00:17:03,852
(dramatic orchestral music)

361
00:17:09,110 --> 00:17:10,110
Hold it, Katy!

362
00:17:10,279 --> 00:17:11,279
Please, stop!

363
00:17:11,614 --> 00:17:12,197
I love you, Katy!

364
00:17:12,489 --> 00:17:14,089
I raised you as if
you were my own child!

365
00:17:15,869 --> 00:17:17,829
Please, Katy, don't make
me shoot my own daughter.

366
00:17:19,080 --> 00:17:20,920
You never answered any
of my questions, Father.

367
00:17:23,334 --> 00:17:24,334
But, Katy.

368
00:17:24,627 --> 00:17:25,627
Japan is crying.

369
00:17:26,503 --> 00:17:28,263
It is my duty to create
a Japan that deserves

370
00:17:29,298 --> 00:17:30,499
the protection of a Kushinada.

371
00:17:31,132 --> 00:17:32,732
But, to do that I must
regress all of the

372
00:17:32,886 --> 00:17:34,806
more advanced life forms
to the most basic level.

373
00:17:35,596 --> 00:17:36,996
Every human must
be transformed into

374
00:17:38,139 --> 00:17:39,139
something I can control.

375
00:17:40,141 --> 00:17:41,141
You're insane!

376
00:17:41,435 --> 00:17:42,636
All human lives must therefore

377
00:17:42,811 --> 00:17:44,132
be reduced to the
level of plants!

378
00:17:45,397 --> 00:17:46,397
Katy!

379
00:17:47,108 --> 00:17:48,988
What do you mean when you
say that you'll reduce

380
00:17:49,735 --> 00:17:51,016
everyone to the level of plants?

381
00:17:52,153 --> 00:17:53,953
I'm not even if what you
say is even possible.

382
00:17:54,991 --> 00:17:56,791
But how could you think
of doing such a thing?

383
00:17:56,868 --> 00:17:58,668
You'd turn Mom and Grandma
and my friend Keiko

384
00:17:59,578 --> 00:18:00,898
and Mr. Kunakita
and Mrs. Takeuchi

385
00:18:01,330 --> 00:18:02,930
and everyone else at
the TAC into plants?

386
00:18:06,251 --> 00:18:06,920
Even Kusanagi?

387
00:18:07,169 --> 00:18:08,250
Turning people into plants?

388
00:18:08,712 --> 00:18:10,352
How could anyone think
of such a horrible,

389
00:18:11,507 --> 00:18:12,173
monstrous thing?

390
00:18:12,257 --> 00:18:13,257
I don't understand!

391
00:18:13,759 --> 00:18:15,319
Kusanagi used to
protect you, didn't he?

392
00:18:16,387 --> 00:18:17,588
And this is how you repay him?

393
00:18:19,682 --> 00:18:20,682
(dramatic music)

394
00:18:30,068 --> 00:18:31,068
(whirring)

395
00:18:31,152 --> 00:18:32,152
Kusanagi!

396
00:18:33,988 --> 00:18:34,238
Ahhh!

397
00:18:34,780 --> 00:18:35,196
Be gone!

398
00:18:35,447 --> 00:18:36,116
Kusanagi!

399
00:18:36,197 --> 00:18:38,077
The time has come for you
to die! (both yelling)

400
00:18:39,576 --> 00:18:40,657
(shouting) Leave him alone!

401
00:18:41,370 --> 00:18:41,870
Aaah!

402
00:18:42,038 --> 00:18:43,223
An insignificant
little bug like you

403
00:18:43,247 --> 00:18:44,647
can't destroy Lord
Susano-Oh's plan!

404
00:18:47,835 --> 00:18:48,835
(laughing maniacally)

405
00:18:50,922 --> 00:18:51,922
(screaming) Kusanagi!

406
00:19:08,229 --> 00:19:09,229
Katy!

407
00:19:13,902 --> 00:19:14,902
(gunshot)

408
00:19:18,407 --> 00:19:19,407
I've got to fly faster!

409
00:19:20,160 --> 00:19:21,160
I must fly faster!

410
00:19:23,704 --> 00:19:24,704
(yelling) Katy!

411
00:19:26,247 --> 00:19:27,247
(whirring)

412
00:19:31,252 --> 00:19:32,252
Why won't you die?

413
00:19:33,714 --> 00:19:34,714
Imperfect soul!

414
00:19:36,633 --> 00:19:37,633
Kusanagi!

415
00:19:39,260 --> 00:19:40,260
Kushinada?

416
00:19:40,304 --> 00:19:41,304
Get back, Momiji!

417
00:19:43,057 --> 00:19:43,474
Kusanagi!

418
00:19:43,640 --> 00:19:45,440
I'm the only one that
can protect a Kushinada.

419
00:19:49,480 --> 00:19:50,480
Kusanagi!

420
00:19:52,483 --> 00:19:53,483
(groaning)

421
00:19:55,569 --> 00:19:56,569
(screaming) Kusanagi!

422
00:20:01,450 --> 00:20:02,450
(rustling)

423
00:20:05,038 --> 00:20:06,038
(dramatic music)

424
00:20:49,330 --> 00:20:50,330
(crashing)

425
00:20:53,211 --> 00:20:54,251
(dramatic music continues)

426
00:21:00,425 --> 00:21:01,342
- [Soldier] Sir, the light!

427
00:21:01,385 --> 00:21:02,779
It's coming from the
construction site

428
00:21:02,803 --> 00:21:03,803
